The paper deals with embedding points in high-dimensional spaces into lower-dimensional spaces while preserving certain distance metrics. This is a problem that is relevant to several areas of computer science, including data structures (cs.DS), information theory (cs.IT), computational geometry (cs.CG), machine learning (cs.LG), and numerical analysis (cs.NA). Given that the paper focuses on the Sparsest Cut problem, which is a fundamental problem in computer science, it is likely to be of interest to researchers in several of these sub-categories.
